Subject: [PATCH v7 12/13] user_events: Validate user payloads for size and null termination
Date:   Thu,  9 Dec 2021 14:32:09 -0800
Message-Id: <20211209223210.1818-13-beaub@linux.microsoft.com>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.17.1
In-Reply-To: <20211209223210.1818-1-beaub@linux.microsoft.com>
References: <20211209223210.1818-1-beaub@linux.microsoft.com>
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org

Add validation to ensure data is at or greater than the min size for the
fields of the event. If a dynamic array is used and is a type of char,
ensure null termination of the array exists. Add unit test cases for the
above scenarios.

Signed-off-by: Beau Belgrave <beaub@linux.microsoft.com>
